    <div class="crowd-tip"><strong>Best time:</strong> Weekday mornings (Mon–Wed, 10:00–11:30) before the first seal feeding draw the largest midday crowds. Arrive at 10:00 opening to see the seals before the 10:30 session fills the viewing area. Saturdays in summer are the busiest — the seal pool galleries can become congested around feeding times. The cinema runs continuously, so there is no fixed queue, but the first morning screening at opening is the least crowded.</div>
